---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Saktimat"
  description="Why Saktimat exists and how it's built."
>

  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16 text-center">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold text-[#1A1A2E] leading-tight tracking-tight mb-5">
      About Saktimat
    </h1>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Saktimat exists -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm p-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#1A1A2E] mb-4">Why Saktimat exists</h2>
      <p class="text-[#3D4259]/80 leading-relaxed">
        Saktimat exists to help people who feel lost find a way back to themselves. Not through advice or instruction, but through quiet, consistent reflection. We believe understanding your own patterns is the first step toward feeling more grounded, more capable, and less alone in figuring things out.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it's grounded in real methods -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm p-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#1A1A2E] mb-6">How it's grounded in real methods</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-[#3D4259]/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p>Saktimat is built around ecological momentary assessment, a research method for capturing how people actually function day to day, in the moment, rather than relying on memory or guesswork weeks later. Most reflection happens in hindsight. Saktimat asks you in real time, so the picture that builds over weeks and months is honest, not reconstructed.</p>
        <p>The principles behind Saktimat are simple: notice without judging, reward showing up again rather than getting it perfect, and let patterns emerge slowly rather than rushing to conclusions. Once your patterns and leaks start to surface, Saktimat shifts from simply observing to actively guiding, helping you build the structure and regulation needed to act on what you've learned about yourself, day by day. It becomes less of a mirror and more of an operating system for how you actually function.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy as a foundation -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm p-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#1A1A2E] mb-4">Privacy as a foundation</h2>
      <p class="text-[#3D4259]/80 leading-relaxed">
        Saktimat was built with privacy as a starting point, not an afterthought. Your check-ins, reflections, and patterns belong to you. Read our full <a href="/privacy" class="text-[#4A90D9] hover:underline">Privacy & Data Guidelines</a> to see exactly how your data is handled.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Saktimat is not -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 pb-24">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm p-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#1A1A2E] mb-6">What Saktimat is not</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-[#3D4259]/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p>Saktimat is not a diagnostic tool, a therapist, or a substitute for professional medical or mental health support. If you're navigating something difficult, we genuinely encourage you to seek support from a qualified professional, alongside using Saktimat, not instead of it.</p>
        <p>We also understand that professional support isn't always accessible to everyone. Saktimat is here to help you build self-awareness and structure either way, whether alongside professional care or in the times when that care is out of reach.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
